    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" subtype="primary" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="grc" resp="#JP" source="https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/4MCP2PVV">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested"><name>Ἀγαθόπο
                    <lb n="2" break="no"/>υς</name></persName> χρη
                    <lb n="3" break="no"/>στὸς καὶ
                   <lb n="4"/><supplied reason="lost">ἄμεμ</supplied>πτος
                    <lb n="5"/><gap reason="illegible" unit="character" extent="unknown"/>
                    <lb n="6"/><gap reason="illegible" unit="character" extent="unknown"/> 
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app><note>Text after Orsi 1912 and a low resolution photograph; fresh study is required</note></app>
                    <app loc="2"><note>It is clear that the text in line 2 is complete, and the name carries over from line 1 to 2, for the more common form Ἀγαθόπους; this further implies that the damage on the right is ancient, preceding inscription.</note></app>
                    <app loc="5"><note>The traces are clearly compatible with some version of ἔζησεν ἔτη</note></app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#JP">
                <p>Agathopous, worthy and blameless [lived...].</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p></p>
            </div>
